---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import { buildArticleSchema, buildBreadcrumbSchema, buildFAQSchema, buildWebSiteSchema } from '../../../lib/seo';

const title = 'RV water intrusion | How to recognize it and what to do';
const description = 'Clinique du VR guide to recognize water intrusion on an RV, travel trailer, or caravan and know what to do before the damage gets worse.';
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What are the first signs of water intrusion in an RV?',
    answer: 'The first signs are often a moisture smell, a water stain, a cracked seal, a warped ceiling, a soft wall, or a swelling floor.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What should I do first if I suspect water intrusion?',
    answer: 'Try to keep the vehicle away from more water exposure, take photos, note the affected areas, and then confirm whether the right next step is inspection, targeted maintenance, or repair.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does water intrusion always mean a major repair?',
    answer: 'Not always. If caught early, seal maintenance or a sealing correction may be enough. Once materials are already affected, repair becomes more likely.'
  }
];
const schemas = [
  buildWebSiteSchema(),
  buildArticleSchema({
    headline: title,
    description,
    path: '/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/'
  }),
  buildFAQSchema(faqs),
  buildBreadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/en/' },
    { name: 'Resources', path: '/en/faq/' },
    { name: 'Water intrusion' }
  ])
];
---

<Layout
  title={`${title} | Clinique du VR`}
  description={description}
  lang="en-CA"
  canonicalPath="/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/"
  frPath="/ressources/infiltration-eau-vr/"
  enPath="/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/"
  schemas={schemas}
  ogType="article"
>
  <Header lang="en" />
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Practical resource</p><h1>RV water intrusion: how to recognize it and what to do</h1><p class="lead">Water intrusion on an RV or trailer does not always begin with a dramatic visible failure. More often, it starts with smaller warning signs that become serious if nothing is done.</p></div></section>
    <section class="content-section"><div class="container content-grid">
      <article class="content-card"><h2>How to recognize water intrusion</h2><p>The most common signs are a moisture smell, a water stain, dry or cracked seals, a warped surface, a soft wall, a swelling floor, or a section of ceiling that no longer looks right. On an RV, intrusion can also hide around openings, roof areas, corners, and trim.</p></article>
      <article class="content-card"><h2>What to check first</h2><p>Wall seals, roof seals, moldings, vulnerable openings, corners, window edges, roof vents, and the roof membrane are among the first places to look. These are often the areas that let water in before damage becomes obvious.</p></article>
      <article class="content-card"><h2>What to do as soon as you suspect it</h2><ol><li>Keep the vehicle sheltered if possible.</li><li>Take photos of visible signs.</li><li>Do not wait for another storm or another season.</li><li>Confirm whether the next useful step is inspection, seal maintenance, or repair.</li></ol></article>
      <article class="content-card"><h2>What to avoid</h2><p>It is better not to hide the symptom too quickly without confirming the real cause. Water intrusion that is poorly understood can continue behind surfaces and turn a still-limited issue into a much more expensive repair file.</p></article>
      <article class="content-card"><h2>When inspection is the right first step</h2><p>Inspection is often the best option when you suspect water intrusion but do not yet know where it is coming from, when several signs point in different directions, or when you want to confirm the vehicle’s actual condition before deciding on work.</p></article>
      <article class="content-card"><h2>When maintenance or repair takes over</h2><p>If the seals or roof mostly show early aging without major visible damage, maintenance may be enough. If water has already reached the materials and surfaces are soft or damaged, repair is usually the logical next step.</p></article>
    </div></section>
    <section class="faq-section"><div class="container"><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list">{faqs.map((item) => (<article class="faq-card"><h3>{item.question}</h3><p>{item.answer}</p></article>))}</div></div></section>
    <section class="links-section"><div class="container links-grid">
      <a class="link-card" href="/en/services/inspection/"><h2>Start with inspection</h2><p>See the inspection page if you want to confirm water intrusion, suspicious seals, or doubts about roof condition.</p><span>View inspection</span></a>
      <a class="link-card" href="/en/services/maintenance/"><h2>See preventive maintenance</h2><p>If the issue still seems limited to seals or sealing work, maintenance may be the right next step.</p><span>View maintenance</span></a>
      <a class="link-card" href="/en/contact/"><h2>Talk to us about your RV</h2><p>Send photos and a short description so we can point you toward the right next step quickly.</p><span>Contact the workshop</span></a>
    </div></section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero { padding: 4.5rem 0 3rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--brand-navy-dark) 0%, #1f476d 60%, #eef3f7 60%, #eef3f7 100%); color: white; }
  .eyebrow { display: inline-flex; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding: 0.45rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 999px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12); color: var(--brand-gold); font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .page-hero h1 { color: white; max-width: 16ch; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lead { max-width: 64ch; color: #e7edf4; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .content-section, .faq-section, .links-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #eef3f7; }
  .faq-section, .links-section { padding-top: 0; }
  .content-grid, .links-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
  .content-card, .faq-card, .link-card { background: white; border-radius: 18px; padding: 1.5rem; box-shadow: 0 12px 26px rgba(20, 36, 55, 0.08); }
  .content-card p, .faq-card p, .link-card p { margin-top: 0.8rem; color: var(--brand-muted); }
  .content-card ol { margin: 0.9rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-muted); }
  .content-card li + li { margin-top: 0.45rem; }
  .faq-list { display: grid; gap: 1rem; }
  .link-card { text-decoration: none; display: grid; grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .link-card span { font-weight: 700; color: var(--brand-navy); }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .page-hero { background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--brand-navy-dark) 0%, #1f476d 100%); padding: 3.8rem 0 2.8rem; } .content-section, .faq-section, .links-section { padding: 3rem 0; } .faq-section, .links-section { padding-top: 0; } }
</style>
